# Environment Variables — LogicFlow Code Review Assistant

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values.
**Never commit `.env` to version control.**

```bash
# ── Required ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Google Gemini Developer API key (preferred path)
# Get yours at: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# ── Optional (Cloud Run / Production) ─────────────────────────────────────────

# GCP Project ID (auto-set on Cloud Run via metadata server)
GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=your_gcp_project_id

# Allowed CORS origin in production (default: allow all)
ALLOWED_ORIGIN=https://your-frontend-domain.example.com

# Node.js environment
NODE_ENV=production

# Port (Cloud Run injects this automatically)
PORT=8080

# ── Google Cloud Secret Manager (optional) ────────────────────────────────────
# If set, the app retrieves GEMINI_API_KEY from Secret Manager instead of the
# env var above.
# Format: projects/{PROJECT_NUMBER}/secrets/{SECRET_NAME}/versions/latest
GEMINI_SECRET_NAME=projects/123456789/secrets/gemini-api-key/versions/latest
```
